item.title: Europe Vows to Step Up Baltic Sea Security After a New Cable Break

item.title: Trudeau Needles Trump as Canadians Revel in Hockey Win
item.description: Canada beat the U.S. in a championship game with added meaning because of political tensions caused by President Trump’s taunts and economic threats.

item.title: MrBeast says built his $700m YouTube empire on the ‘purple cow effect’
item.description: MrBeast, aka Jimmy Donaldson, has cracked the code for YouTube stardom—but says his success won't be easy to replicate.

item.title: Yankees Part With Tradition: Beards Are Now Allowed
item.description: The team is ending its longstanding policy on facial hair and will allow “well-groomed beards moving forward,” Hal Steinbrenner said.

item.title: Tesla recalls more than 375,000 vehicles due to power steering issue
item.description: The loss of power could require more effort to control the car by drivers, particularly at low speeds, increasing the risk of a crash.

item.title: Coinbase Says S.E.C. Will Drop Crypto Lawsuit
item.description: The end of a court fight with the largest U.S. crypto company would be a big win for an industry that financially backed President Trump.

item.title: Trump Media board approves an investment fund to explore acquisitions
item.description: Trump Media wants to add more businesses in what it calls the “America First Economy,” according to an SEC filing.
